## Cross‑Cutting Concepts

### Ownership (See `00_core_ownership.md`)
- Every operational entity has exactly one owner (Team or Organisation).
- Ownership is **immutable** after creation.
- Inventory uses a direct `team_id` foreign key; other domains use polymorphic `(owner_type, owner_id)`.

### Moderation
- All new products (except category `Other`) enter a moderation queue.
- Only internal Getti staff (Platform Domain) can moderate.
- Moderation affects **visibility**, never rewrites inventory history.

### Snapshots
- Product attributes (weight, volume) are frozen at the time of inventory counting.
- Recipe ingredients are frozen at the time of breakdown.
- Snapshots are stored directly in the inventory item row.

---

## Architectural Invariants

> Inventory counts Product Variants – never Product Labels or Recipes directly.  
> History is immutable – once a session is finished, data never changes.  
> Users act; Teams/Organisations own.  
> AS‑IS over TO‑BE – current operations are never blocked by future aspirations.  
> Monetisation must not break operational integrity.

